c10t
------------------------------------------
I wrote c10t entirely because i liked the tool Cartograph by ZomBuster, but I
wasn't too fond of a couple of aspects about how rendering was performed.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.10-1
  libboost_filesystem1.66-1.66.0-1
  libfreetype6-2.13.3-1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libpng16-1.6.47-2
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1
  libunc1-1.0+git20120507-1bl1
  zlib0-1.3.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  libboost-devel-1.66.0-1
  libfreetype-devel-2.13.3-1
  libpng-devel-1.6.47-2
  libunc-devel-1.0+git20120507-1bl1
  ninja-1.13.2-1
  zlib-devel-1.3.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/udoprog/c10t

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/udoprog/c10t/archive/4b9cb2e173f1d687105e9095be9f0b653f27e9f1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack c10t-1.7+git20240711-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./c10t-1.7+git20240711-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/c10t-1.7+git20240711-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/c10t-1.7+git20240711-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(c10t)
  /usr/bin/c10t.exe
  /usr/share/c10t/NBT.txt
  /usr/share/c10t/bigtest.nbt
  /usr/share/c10t/test.nbt
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/c10t.README
  /usr/share/doc/c10t/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/c10t/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/c10t/README.md

